Deputy President William Ruto has lauded his running
mate Rigathi Gachagua’s performance at the Deputy Presidential Debate on
Tuesday night. Taking to
social media, the Kenya Kwanza flag bearer appreciated Gachagua saying he had
proved to Kenyans his capability to hold the second office in the land come
August. “Congratulations
Rigathi Gachagua my very able running mate. Kenyans are confident that in you
we have a seasoned, passionate and focused leader to help us steer Kenya Kwanza
to victory and the nation to prosperity,” Ruto wrote on Twitter. “We thank
Almighty God na ubarikiwe saaana. Never mind the media.” In the debate
held at Catholic Universit of Eastern Africa on Tuesday night, Gachagua faced
off with Azimio la Umoja One Kenya deputy president candidate Martha Karua.  Roots
Party candidate Justina Wamae likewise encountered Agano party’s Ruth Mucheru
Mutua. 